36const int64_t kRtpRtcpMaxIdleTimeProcessMs = 5;
37const int64_t kRtpRtcpRttProcessTimeMs = 1000;
38const int64_t kRtpRtcpBitrateProcessTimeMs = 10;
39const int64_t kDefaultExpectedRetransmissionTimeMs = 125;

42ModuleRtpRtcpImpl::RtpSenderContext::RtpSenderContext(
43 const RtpRtcpInterface::Configuration& config)
44 : packet_history(config.clock, config.enable_rtx_padding_prioritization),
45 packet_sender(config, &packet_history),
46 non_paced_sender(&packet_sender),

52std::unique_ptr<RtpRtcp> RtpRtcp::DEPRECATED_Create(
53 const Configuration& configuration) {
54 RTC_DCHECK(configuration.clock);
55 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
56 << "*********** USING WebRTC INTERNAL IMPLEMENTATION DETAILS ***********";
57 return std::make_unique<ModuleRtpRtcpImpl>(configuration);
58}

60ModuleRtpRtcpImpl::ModuleRtpRtcpImpl(const Configuration& configuration)
61 : rtcp_sender_(configuration),
62 rtcp_receiver_(configuration, this),
63 clock_(configuration.clock),
64 last_bitrate_process_time_(clock_->TimeInMilliseconds()),
65 last_rtt_process_time_(clock_->TimeInMilliseconds()),
66 next_process_time_(clock_->TimeInMilliseconds() +
67 kRtpRtcpMaxIdleTimeProcessMs),
68 packet_overhead_(28), // IPV4 UDP.
69 nack_last_time_sent_full_ms_(0),
70 nack_last_seq_number_sent_(0),
71 remote_bitrate_(configuration.remote_bitrate_estimator),
72 rtt_stats_(configuration.rtt_stats),
73 rtt_ms_(0) {
74 if (!configuration.receiver_only) {
75 rtp_sender_ = std::make_unique<RtpSenderContext>(configuration);
76 // Make sure rtcp sender use same timestamp offset as rtp sender.
77 rtcp_sender_.SetTimestampOffset(
78 rtp_sender_->packet_generator.TimestampOffset());
79 }
80
81 // Set default packet size limit.
82 // TODO(nisse): Kind-of duplicates
83 // webrtc::VideoSendStream::Config::Rtp::kDefaultMaxPacketSize.
84 const size_t kTcpOverIpv4HeaderSize = 40;
85 SetMaxRtpPacketSize(IP_PACKET_SIZE - kTcpOverIpv4HeaderSize);
86}

88ModuleRtpRtcpImpl::~ModuleRtpRtcpImpl() = default;

90// Returns the number of milliseconds until the module want a worker thread
91// to call Process.
92int64_t ModuleRtpRtcpImpl::TimeUntilNextProcess() {
93 return std::max<int64_t>(0,
94 next_process_time_ - clock_->TimeInMilliseconds());
95}
96
97// Process any pending tasks such as timeouts (non time critical events).
98void ModuleRtpRtcpImpl::Process() {
99 const int64_t now = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
100 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11581): Figure out why we need to call Process() 200
101 // times a second.
102 next_process_time_ = now + kRtpRtcpMaxIdleTimeProcessMs;
103
104 if (rtp_sender_) {
105 if (now >= last_bitrate_process_time_ + kRtpRtcpBitrateProcessTimeMs) {
106 rtp_sender_->packet_sender.ProcessBitrateAndNotifyObservers();
107 last_bitrate_process_time_ = now;
108 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11581): Is this a bug? At the top of the function,
109 // next_process_time_ is incremented by 5ms, here we effectively do a
110 // std::min() of (now + 5ms, now + 10ms). Seems like this is a no-op?
111 next_process_time_ =
112 std::min(next_process_time_, now + kRtpRtcpBitrateProcessTimeMs);
113 }
114 }
115
116 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11581): We update the RTT once a second, whereas other
117 // things that run in this method are updated much more frequently. Move the
118 // RTT checking over to the worker thread, which matches better with where the
119 // stats are maintained.
120 bool process_rtt = now >= last_rtt_process_time_ + kRtpRtcpRttProcessTimeMs;
121 if (rtcp_sender_.Sending()) {
122 // Process RTT if we have received a report block and we haven't
123 // processed RTT for at least |kRtpRtcpRttProcessTimeMs| milliseconds.
124 // Note that LastReceivedReportBlockMs() grabs a lock, so check
125 // |process_rtt| first.
126 if (process_rtt && rtt_stats_ != nullptr &&
127 rtcp_receiver_.LastReceivedReportBlockMs() > last_rtt_process_time_) {
128 int64_t max_rtt_ms = 0;
129 for (const auto& block : rtcp_receiver_.GetLatestReportBlockData()) {
130 if (block.last_rtt_ms() > max_rtt_ms) {
131 max_rtt_ms = block.last_rtt_ms();
132 }
133 }
134 // Report the rtt.
135 if (max_rtt_ms > 0) {
136 rtt_stats_->OnRttUpdate(max_rtt_ms);
137 }
138 }
139
140 // Verify receiver reports are delivered and the reported sequence number
141 // is increasing.
142 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11581): The timeout value needs to be checked every
143 // few seconds (see internals of RtcpRrTimeout). Here, we may be polling it
144 // a couple of hundred times a second, which isn't great since it grabs a
145 // lock. Note also that LastReceivedReportBlockMs() (called above) and
146 // RtcpRrTimeout() both grab the same lock and check the same timer, so
147 // it should be possible to consolidate that work somehow.
148 if (rtcp_receiver_.RtcpRrTimeout()) {
149 RTC_LOG_F(LS_WARNING) << "Timeout: No RTCP RR received.";
150 } else if (rtcp_receiver_.RtcpRrSequenceNumberTimeout()) {
151 RTC_LOG_F(LS_WARNING) << "Timeout: No increase in RTCP RR extended "
152 "highest sequence number.";
153 }
154
155 if (remote_bitrate_ && rtcp_sender_.TMMBR()) {
156 unsigned int target_bitrate = 0;
157 std::vector<unsigned int> ssrcs;
158 if (remote_bitrate_->LatestEstimate(&ssrcs, &target_bitrate)) {
159 if (!ssrcs.empty()) {
160 target_bitrate = target_bitrate / ssrcs.size();
161 }
162 rtcp_sender_.SetTargetBitrate(target_bitrate);
163 }
164 }
165 } else {
166 // Report rtt from receiver.
167 if (process_rtt) {
168 int64_t rtt_ms;
169 if (rtt_stats_ && rtcp_receiver_.GetAndResetXrRrRtt(&rtt_ms)) {
170 rtt_stats_->OnRttUpdate(rtt_ms);
171 }
172 }
173 }
174
175 // Get processed rtt.
176 if (process_rtt) {
177 last_rtt_process_time_ = now;
178 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11581): Is this a bug? At the top of the function,
179 // next_process_time_ is incremented by 5ms, here we effectively do a
180 // std::min() of (now + 5ms, now + 1000ms). Seems like this is a no-op?
181 next_process_time_ = std::min(
182 next_process_time_, last_rtt_process_time_ + kRtpRtcpRttProcessTimeMs);
183 if (rtt_stats_) {
184 // Make sure we have a valid RTT before setting.
185 int64_t last_rtt = rtt_stats_->LastProcessedRtt();
186 if (last_rtt >= 0)
187 set_rtt_ms(last_rtt);
188 }
189 }
190
191 if (rtcp_sender_.TimeToSendRTCPReport())
192 rtcp_sender_.SendRTCP(GetFeedbackState(), kRtcpReport);
193
194 if (rtcp_sender_.TMMBR() && rtcp_receiver_.UpdateTmmbrTimers()) {
195 rtcp_receiver_.NotifyTmmbrUpdated();
196 }
197}

295// TODO(pbos): Handle media and RTX streams separately (separate RTCP
296// feedbacks).
297RTCPSender::FeedbackState ModuleRtpRtcpImpl::GetFeedbackState() {
298 RTCPSender::FeedbackState state;
299 // This is called also when receiver_only is true. Hence below
300 // checks that rtp_sender_ exists.
301 if (rtp_sender_) {
302 StreamDataCounters rtp_stats;
303 StreamDataCounters rtx_stats;
304 rtp_sender_->packet_sender.GetDataCounters(&rtp_stats, &rtx_stats);
305 state.packets_sent =
306 rtp_stats.transmitted.packets + rtx_stats.transmitted.packets;
307 state.media_bytes_sent = rtp_stats.transmitted.payload_bytes +
308 rtx_stats.transmitted.payload_bytes;
309 state.send_bitrate =
310 rtp_sender_->packet_sender.GetSendRates().Sum().bps<uint32_t>();
311 }
312 state.receiver = &rtcp_receiver_;
313
314 uint32_t received_ntp_secs = 0;
315 uint32_t received_ntp_frac = 0;
316 state.remote_sr = 0;
317 if (rtcp_receiver_.NTP(&received_ntp_secs, &received_ntp_frac,
318 /*rtcp_arrival_time_secs=*/&state.last_rr_ntp_secs,
319 /*rtcp_arrival_time_frac=*/&state.last_rr_ntp_frac,
320 /*rtcp_timestamp=*/nullptr,
321 /*remote_sender_packet_count=*/nullptr,
322 /*remote_sender_octet_count=*/nullptr,
323 /*remote_sender_reports_count=*/nullptr)) {
324 state.remote_sr = ((received_ntp_secs & 0x0000ffff) << 16) +
325 ((received_ntp_frac & 0xffff0000) >> 16);
326 }
327
328 state.last_xr_rtis = rtcp_receiver_.ConsumeReceivedXrReferenceTimeInfo();
329
330 return state;
331}

373
374bool ModuleRtpRtcpImpl::OnSendingRtpFrame(uint32_t timestamp,
375 int64_t capture_time_ms,
376 int payload_type,
377 bool force_sender_report) {
378 if (!Sending())
379 return false;
380
381 rtcp_sender_.SetLastRtpTime(timestamp, capture_time_ms, payload_type);
382 // Make sure an RTCP report isn't queued behind a key frame.
383 if (rtcp_sender_.TimeToSendRTCPReport(force_sender_report))
384 rtcp_sender_.SendRTCP(GetFeedbackState(), kRtcpReport);
385
386 return true;
387}

397 return true;

493// Get RoundTripTime.
494int32_t ModuleRtpRtcpImpl::RTT(const uint32_t remote_ssrc,
495 int64_t* rtt,
496 int64_t* avg_rtt,
497 int64_t* min_rtt,
498 int64_t* max_rtt) const {
499 int32_t ret = rtcp_receiver_.RTT(remote_ssrc, rtt, avg_rtt, min_rtt, max_rtt);
500 if (rtt && *rtt == 0) {
501 // Try to get RTT from RtcpRttStats class.
502 *rtt = rtt_ms();
503 }
504 return ret;
505}
506
507int64_t ModuleRtpRtcpImpl::ExpectedRetransmissionTimeMs() const {
508 int64_t expected_retransmission_time_ms = rtt_ms();
509 if (expected_retransmission_time_ms > 0) {
510 return expected_retransmission_time_ms;
511 }
512 // No rtt available (|kRtpRtcpRttProcessTimeMs| not yet passed?), so try to
513 // poll avg_rtt_ms directly from rtcp receiver.
514 if (rtcp_receiver_.RTT(rtcp_receiver_.RemoteSSRC(), nullptr,
515 &expected_retransmission_time_ms, nullptr,
516 nullptr) == 0) {
517 return expected_retransmission_time_ms;
518 }
519 return kDefaultExpectedRetransmissionTimeMs;
520}

540absl::optional<RtpRtcpInterface::SenderReportStats>
541ModuleRtpRtcpImpl::GetSenderReportStats() const {
542 SenderReportStats stats;
543 uint32_t remote_timestamp_secs;
544 uint32_t remote_timestamp_frac;
545 uint32_t arrival_timestamp_secs;
546 uint32_t arrival_timestamp_frac;
547 if (rtcp_receiver_.NTP(&remote_timestamp_secs, &remote_timestamp_frac,
548 &arrival_timestamp_secs, &arrival_timestamp_frac,
549 /*rtcp_timestamp=*/nullptr, &stats.packets_sent,
550 &stats.bytes_sent, &stats.reports_count)) {
551 stats.last_remote_timestamp.Set(remote_timestamp_secs,
552 remote_timestamp_frac);
553 stats.last_arrival_timestamp.Set(arrival_timestamp_secs,
554 arrival_timestamp_frac);
555 return stats;
556 }
557 return absl::nullopt;
558}

594// Send a Negative acknowledgment packet.
595int32_t ModuleRtpRtcpImpl::SendNACK(const uint16_t* nack_list,
596 const uint16_t size) {
597 uint16_t nack_length = size;
598 uint16_t start_id = 0;
599 int64_t now_ms = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
600 if (TimeToSendFullNackList(now_ms)) {
601 nack_last_time_sent_full_ms_ = now_ms;
602 } else {
603 // Only send extended list.
604 if (nack_last_seq_number_sent_ == nack_list[size - 1]) {
605 // Last sequence number is the same, do not send list.
606 return 0;
607 }
608 // Send new sequence numbers.
609 for (int i = 0; i < size; ++i) {
610 if (nack_last_seq_number_sent_ == nack_list[i]) {
611 start_id = i + 1;
612 break;
613 }
614 }
615 nack_length = size - start_id;
616 }
617
618 // Our RTCP NACK implementation is limited to kRtcpMaxNackFields sequence
619 // numbers per RTCP packet.
620 if (nack_length > kRtcpMaxNackFields) {
621 nack_length = kRtcpMaxNackFields;
622 }
623 nack_last_seq_number_sent_ = nack_list[start_id + nack_length - 1];
624
625 return rtcp_sender_.SendRTCP(GetFeedbackState(), kRtcpNack, nack_length,
626 &nack_list[start_id]);
627}
628
629void ModuleRtpRtcpImpl::SendNack(
630 const std::vector<uint16_t>& sequence_numbers) {
631 rtcp_sender_.SendRTCP(GetFeedbackState(), kRtcpNack, sequence_numbers.size(),
632 sequence_numbers.data());
633}
634
635bool ModuleRtpRtcpImpl::TimeToSendFullNackList(int64_t now) const {
636 // Use RTT from RtcpRttStats class if provided.
637 int64_t rtt = rtt_ms();
638 if (rtt == 0) {
639 rtcp_receiver_.RTT(rtcp_receiver_.RemoteSSRC(), NULL, &rtt, NULL, NULL);
640 }
641
642 const int64_t kStartUpRttMs = 100;
643 int64_t wait_time = 5 + ((rtt * 3) >> 1); // 5 + RTT * 1.5.
644 if (rtt == 0) {
645 wait_time = kStartUpRttMs;
646 }
647
648 // Send a full NACK list once within every |wait_time|.
649 return now - nack_last_time_sent_full_ms_ > wait_time;
650}

693
694void ModuleRtpRtcpImpl::OnReceivedNack(
695 const std::vector<uint16_t>& nack_sequence_numbers) {
696 if (!rtp_sender_)
697 return;
698
699 if (!StorePackets() || nack_sequence_numbers.empty()) {
700 return;
701 }
702 // Use RTT from RtcpRttStats class if provided.
703 int64_t rtt = rtt_ms();
704 if (rtt == 0) {
705 rtcp_receiver_.RTT(rtcp_receiver_.RemoteSSRC(), NULL, &rtt, NULL, NULL);
706 }
707 rtp_sender_->packet_generator.OnReceivedNack(nack_sequence_numbers, rtt);
708}
709
710void ModuleRtpRtcpImpl::OnReceivedRtcpReportBlocks(
711 const ReportBlockList& report_blocks) {
712 if (rtp_sender_) {
713 uint32_t ssrc = SSRC();
714 absl::optional<uint32_t> rtx_ssrc;
715 if (rtp_sender_->packet_generator.RtxStatus() != kRtxOff) {
716 rtx_ssrc = rtp_sender_->packet_generator.RtxSsrc();
717 }
718
719 for (const RTCPReportBlock& report_block : report_blocks) {
720 if (ssrc == report_block.source_ssrc) {
721 rtp_sender_->packet_generator.OnReceivedAckOnSsrc(
722 report_block.extended_highest_sequence_number);
723 } else if (rtx_ssrc && *rtx_ssrc == report_block.source_ssrc) {
724 rtp_sender_->packet_generator.OnReceivedAckOnRtxSsrc(
725 report_block.extended_highest_sequence_number);
726 }
727 }
728 }
729}

738 }
739}
